(27320, 1476, 2710, 1, 'A night in Madrid', '', '2010-08-20 00:00:00', 2010, 0, 1, 6, 'Last time we talked all night, \r\nwhen we''re young, not worried about the time\r\nLaying in the dark we chatted\r\nabout our lives, and nonsense around us\r\nI didn''t know why exactly it\r\nseemed so quite, and unpretentious\r\nvoices filled up the space\r\nfortify our fragile hearts\r\n\r\nI said to you ''I''m feeling slack''\r\nyou dropped the silence as you''re asleep\r\nI added extended details up \r\nsuddenly you just signed\r\nand you turned over to my direction \r\n''you will be alright''\r\nwhen we heard a clock bell rang again\r\noh! it''s getting late\r\n\r\nthen at the break of dawn\r\nwe realized we hadn''t had some sleep all night\r\nthe breakfast time had come\r\nChurros and chocolate at Ohlàlà\r\nUnder the morning sun \r\nironically we felt so tired\r\nbut we''re so satisfied\r\nsmiles on our faces, the words in our minds\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nDo you remember there''s one night\r\nunexpectedly we went out for some fun\r\nafter few drinks you felt so high\r\nflying hairs, you could barely stand still\r\nhip-hop rhythm, techno beats\r\nyou yelled out lyrics and howled so loud and wild\r\nit was such a wonderful night\r\nbut nothing''s better than we just talked all night\r\n\r\nit needs courages and coincidence \r\nwhen we just feel it''s alright \r\nwhen we are ready to be hearty\r\nspontaneously \r\nit maybe only happen one time\r\nor it never comes\r\nwe find windows glints in the sun,\r\nwe have talked all night\r\n\r\nthen at the break of dawn\r\nwe realized we hadn''t had some sleep all night\r\nthe breakfast time had come\r\nChurros and chocolate at Ohlàlà\r\nUnder the morning sun \r\nironically we felt so tired\r\nbut we''re so satisfied\r\nsmiles on our faces, the words in our minds', '', 202, '', '', '', '', '', '', 0, 0, 1, '2010-08-24 20:01:58', '2013-10-07 17:16:54', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
